I12(10) The term ``key resources'' means publicly or privately controlled resources essential to the minimal operations of the economy and government.

I12(11) The term ``local government'' means_

I13(A) a county, municipality, city, town, township, local public authority, school district, special district, intrastate district, council of governments (regardless of whether the council of governments is incorporated as a nonprofit corporation under State law), regional or interstate government entity, or agency or instrumentality of a local government;

I13(B) an Indian tribe or authorized tribal organization, or in Alaska a Native village or Alaska Regional Native Corporation; and

I13(C) a rural community, unincorporated town or village, or other public entity.

Q04

I12(12) The term ``major disaster'' has the meaning given in section 5122(2) of title 42.

I12(13) The term ``personnel'' means officers and employees.

I12(14) The term ``Secretary'' means the Secretary of Homeland Security.

I12(15) The term ``State'' means any State of the United States, the District of Columbia, the Commonwealth of Puerto Rico, the Virgin Islands, Guam, American Samoa, the Commonwealth of the Northern Mariana Islands, and any possession of the United States.

I12(16) The term ``terrorism'' means any activity that_

I13(A) involves an act that_

I14(i) is dangerous to human life or potentially destructive of critical infrastructure or key resources; and

I14(ii) is a violation of the criminal laws of the United States or of any State or other subdivision of the United States; and

