I13(A) on an ongoing basis, monitor the availability and appropriateness of surveillance systems used by the NBIC and those systems that could enhance biological situational awareness or the overall performance of the NBIC;

I13(B) on an ongoing basis, review and seek to improve the statistical and other analytical methods used by the NBIC;

I13(C) receive and consider other relevant homeland security information, as appropriate; and

I13(D) provide technical assistance, as appropriate, to all Federal, regional, State, local, and tribal government entities and private sector entities that contribute data relevant to the operation of the NBIC.

I79(2) Assessments

I12The Directing Officer of the NBIC shall_

I13(A) on an ongoing basis, evaluate available data for evidence of a biological event of national concern; and

I13(B) integrate homeland security information with NBIC data to provide overall situational awareness and determine whether a biological event of national concern has occurred.

