I74Findings and Declaration of Purposes

I21Pub. L. 112ÿ09205, ÿ1A2, Dec. 7, 2012, 126 Stat. 1487, provided that: ``Congress finds the following:

I22``(1) The Department of Homeland Security's (DHS) overriding mission is to lead a unified national effort to protect the United States. United States Immigration and Customs Enforcement (ICE) is the largest investigative agency within DHS and is charged with enforcing a wide array of laws, including laws related to securing the border and combating criminal smuggling.

I22``(2) Mexico's northern border with the United States has experienced a dramatic surge in border crime and violence in recent years due to intense competition between Mexican drug cartels and criminal smuggling organizations that employ predatory tactics to realize their profits.

I22``(3) Law enforcement agencies at the United States northern border also face challenges from transnational smuggling organizations.

