I19(a) Audits of grant programs

I79(1) Compliance requirements

I18(A) Audit requirement

I13Each recipient of a grant administered by the Department that expends not less than $500,000 in Federal funds during its fiscal year shall submit to the Administrator a copy of the organization-wide financial and compliance audit report required under chapter 75 of title 31.

I18(B) Access to information

I13The Department and each recipient of a grant administered by the Department shall provide the Comptroller General and any officer or employee of the Government Accountability Office with full access to information regarding the activities carried out related to any grant administered by the Department.

I18(C) Improper payments

I13Consistent with the Improper Payments Information Act of 2002 (31 U.S.C. 3321 note), for each of the grant programs under sections 604 and 605 of this title and section 762 of this title, the Administrator shall specify policies and procedures for_

I14(i) identifying activities funded under any such grant program that are susceptible to significant improper payments; and

I14(ii) reporting any improper payments to the Department.

I79(2) Agency program review

I18(A) In general

I13Not less than once every 2 years, the Administrator shall conduct, for each State and high-risk urban area receiving a grant administered by the Department, a programmatic and financial review of all grants awarded by the Department to prevent, prepare for, protect against, or respond to natural disasters, acts of terrorism, or other man-made disasters, excluding assistance provided under section 203, title IV, or title V of the Robert T. Stafford Disaster Relief and Emergency Assistance Act (42 U.S.C. 5133, 5170 et seq., and 5191 et seq.).

I18(B) Contents

I13Each review under subparagraph (A) shall, at a minimum, examine_

I14(i) whether the funds awarded were used in accordance with the law, program guidance, and State homeland security plans or other applicable plans; and

I14(ii) the extent to which funds awarded enhanced the ability of a grantee to prevent, prepare for, protect against, and respond to natural disasters, acts of terrorism, and other man-made disasters.

I18(C) Authorization of appropriations

I13In addition to any other amounts authorized to be appropriated to the Administrator, there are authorized to be appropriated to the Administrator for reviews under this paragraph_

I14(i) $8,000,000 for each of fiscal years 2008, 2009, and 2010; and

I14(ii) such sums as are necessary for fiscal year 2011, and each fiscal year thereafter.

I79(3) Office of Inspector General performance audits

I18(A) In general

I13In order to ensure the effective and appropriate use of grants administered by the Department, the Inspector General of the Department each year shall conduct audits of a sample of States and high-risk urban areas that receive grants administered by the Department to prevent, prepare for, protect against, or respond to natural disasters, acts of terrorism, or other man-made disasters, excluding assistance provided under section 203, title IV, or title V of the Robert T. Stafford Disaster Relief and Emergency Assistance Act (42 U.S.C. 5133, 5170 et seq., and 5191 et seq.).

I18(B) Determining samples

I13The sample selected for audits under subparagraph (A) shall be_

I14(i) of an appropriate size to_

I16(I) assess the overall integrity of the grant programs described in subparagraph (A); and

I16(II) act as a deterrent to financial mismanagement; and

Q04

I14(ii) selected based on_

I16(I) the size of the grants awarded to the recipient;

I16(II) the past grant management performance of the recipient;

I16(III) concerns identified by the Administrator, including referrals from the Administrator; and

I16(IV) such other factors as determined by the Inspector General of the Department.

I18(C) Comprehensive auditing

I13During the 7-year period beginning on August 3, 2007, the Inspector General of the Department shall conduct not fewer than 1 audit of each State that receives funds under a grant under section 604 or 605 of this title.

I18(D) Report by the Inspector General

I77(i) In general

I14The Inspector General of the Department shall submit to the appropriate committees of Congress an annual consolidated report regarding the audits completed during the fiscal year before the date of that report.

I77(ii) Contents

I14Each report submitted under clause (i) shall describe, for the fiscal year before the date of that report_

I16(I) the audits conducted under subparagraph (A);

I16(II) the findings of the Inspector General with respect to the audits conducted under subparagraph (A);

I16(III) whether the funds awarded were used in accordance with the law, program guidance, and State homeland security plans and other applicable plans; and

I16(IV) the extent to which funds awarded enhanced the ability of a grantee to prevent, prepare for, protect against, and respond to natural disasters, acts of terrorism and other man-made disasters.

